SIMPLE: embarrassed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: embarrassed
<hw>embarrassed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>feeling uneasily
or unpleasantly self-conscious due to some event or circumstance;
<as>as, she was <ex>embarrassed</ex> by her child's
tantrums</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> abashed, self-conscious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>feeling inferior or unworthy and hence unpleasantly
self-conscious; <as>as, too <ex>embarrassed</ex> to say hello to his
drunken father on the street</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> chagrined, mortified.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>embarrassing</ent>⟦br⟧
